WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:02,950
A practical leadership workflow for data and analytics that teams will use 03040530 sounds strategic, but the real constraint is operating behavior in the workflow.

00:03,000 --> 00:05,950
So the context shifts quickly: content moves fast, but behavior change moves slower. Last week in the weekly operations standup, the blocker was not motivation.

00:06,000 --> 00:08,950
Problem one: content is abundant, while reliable follow-through is still scarce.

00:09,000 --> 00:11,950
So run one compact loop: brief, prototype, test with a small audience, then review evidence.

00:12,000 --> 00:14,950
Then launch a refined version inside one focused week, not after a long cycle.

00:15,000 --> 00:17,950
Problem two: once roles shift, old support models no longer fit live execution.

00:18,000 --> 00:20,950
So where does data fit when business transformation, not content volume, is the main game?

00:21,000 --> 00:29,950
What do you think?
